doc.after: MediaWiki supports rich content generated through specialized syntax For example the software comes with optional support for rendering mathematical formulas using LaTeX and a special parser written in OCaml Similar functionality for other content ranging from graphical timelines over mathematical plotting and musical scores to Egyptian hieroglyphs is available in the form of extensions and also aesthetic sense has improved considerably
